16/07/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- Montenegrin Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic has called for intensified co-operation with Albania, in a letter sent to the leader of the Albanian opposition Socialist Movement for Integration and former Albanian Prime Minister Ilir Meta, on Friday (14 July).
Djukanovic stressed that enhancing bilateral ties would help their respective EU bids.
He suggested opening an Albanian embassy in Podgorica would be a concrete step in this direction.
(Albanian News - 15/07/06;
RFE - 14/07/06)
